WEBVTT

00:01.751 --> 00:04.671
- Everybody, lunch boxes out of
backpacks and next to sink.

00:07.590 --> 00:09.467
Excuse me, boys,
what did I just say?

00:09.551 --> 00:12.595
- Don't know. Couldn't listen.
Low blood sugar.

00:12.679 --> 00:14.097
- I'm just walking in.

00:14.180 --> 00:16.056
Seriously spooky.

00:16.140 --> 00:18.351
Noah and I just got home
at the exact same time.

00:18.435 --> 00:19.644
- Oh, that's nice.

00:19.728 --> 00:20.603
Now you can say goodbye to him
at the exact same time

00:20.687 --> 00:22.814
so you can get ready for tennis.

00:22.897 --> 00:24.774
- I quit. Total time suck.

00:24.858 --> 00:28.111
Besides, Noah says
tennis is such a racket.

00:28.194 --> 00:29.487
You get it?

00:29.571 --> 00:31.781
He's so clever.
You are so clever.

00:31.865 --> 00:32.782
- Bye, Noah.

00:32.866 --> 00:36.453
Gabby, did you quit
tennis for Noah?

00:36.536 --> 00:41.916
- No, no. I quit tennis for me--
me spending more time with Noah.

00:42.000 --> 00:43.918
- She also quit yearbook
and drama club.

00:44.002 --> 00:45.044
- And putting on makeup.

00:45.128 --> 00:46.796
- No, I didn't.
I'm wearing some right now.

00:46.880 --> 00:48.923
- Really? That's with makeup?

00:50.717 --> 00:52.260
- Gabby, you can't just give up

00:52.343 --> 00:55.972
your whole life for some guy--
aye, aye!

00:56.055 --> 00:58.767
Did something curl up and die
in your backpack?

00:58.850 --> 00:59.642
- Coach made me take
home my gym clothes.

00:59.726 --> 01:02.812
The janitor filed a grievance.

01:04.563 --> 01:06.483
- James, how long have you
been wearing those?

01:06.566 --> 01:08.359
- Since Tuesday.

01:08.443 --> 01:10.487
- Well, a Tuesday.

01:11.905 --> 01:13.490
- Yeah, she's trippin'.

01:13.573 --> 01:14.657
- Gabby, what are you doing?

01:14.741 --> 01:16.951
- Not much. What are you doing?

01:17.035 --> 01:18.119
- Give me that.

01:18.203 --> 01:20.747
- I am not going
to let this boy run your life.

01:20.830 --> 01:22.123
- I need you to sign this.

01:22.207 --> 01:24.042
- Look, I like Noah.

01:24.125 --> 01:26.544
But there is you time and then
there's you and him time.

01:26.628 --> 01:30.799
And you can't--Aaron, you only
got four out of 10 right

01:30.882 --> 01:31.966
on your spelling test?

01:32.050 --> 01:34.135
I told you to study for this.

01:34.219 --> 01:38.181
- Well, I was going to,
but then...

01:38.264 --> 01:39.682
smoke bomb!

01:42.769 --> 01:44.187
- Uh, dude, for that to work,

01:44.270 --> 01:47.190
you need
to have an actual smoke bomb.

01:47.273 --> 01:49.484
- Uh, dude, I'm nine.

01:49.567 --> 01:52.570
Where am I gonna
get an actual smoke bomb?

01:53.947 --> 01:55.990
[knock at door]

01:57.909 --> 01:58.952
- Hey, howdy neighbor.

01:59.035 --> 02:01.454
Do you have two eggs
you can let go for a quarter?

02:01.538 --> 02:04.290
- Sure, Eunice, but I don't feel
right taking a quarter.

02:04.374 --> 02:07.460
- Oh... you drive
a hard bargain.

02:08.711 --> 02:11.798
Hoyt has two coddled eggs
every day at 4:00 p.m.

02:11.881 --> 02:14.050
He loves his 4:00 coddling.

02:14.133 --> 02:15.718
Thank you.

02:15.802 --> 02:17.679
- It's 4:06, woman.

02:17.762 --> 02:18.972
Coddle me.

02:21.558 --> 02:22.642
- There's my cue.

02:22.725 --> 02:24.853
- Really? If Charlie talked to
me like that,

02:24.936 --> 02:27.397
I'd scramble his eggs.

02:27.480 --> 02:28.940
- Thanks for the girl time.

02:31.818 --> 02:33.570
- No, I can blow off Molly
if you want to do something.

02:33.653 --> 02:34.946
- Seriously, Gabby?

02:35.029 --> 02:36.406
- Why are you looking at me?

02:36.489 --> 02:37.699
Aaron doesn't study.

02:37.782 --> 02:39.284
- Yeah? Well, James smells bad.

02:39.367 --> 02:40.451
- Aren't we more concerned

02:40.535 --> 02:42.829
that Gabby doesn't have a mind
of her own?

02:42.912 --> 02:45.415
- Gabby, get off that phone
with that boy.

02:45.498 --> 02:46.875
Aaron, do some homework.

02:46.958 --> 02:49.919
And, James, go bury
those gym clothes right now!

02:50.003 --> 02:53.423
- All right, Steph...
we'll do it in a minute.

02:53.506 --> 02:56.843
- Yeah, don't worry about it.
She's still trippin'.

02:56.926 --> 02:59.345
[knock at door]

03:00.013 --> 03:01.973
- I've taken your advice,
and I've left Hoyt.

03:05.685 --> 03:06.936
- My advice?

03:07.020 --> 03:09.439
- Yes, you said
that his overbearing behavior

03:09.522 --> 03:11.441
is crippling my growth
as a woman

03:11.524 --> 03:13.276
and it's time for my lady limbs

03:13.359 --> 03:14.777
to reach out for the heavens
and say,

03:14.861 --> 03:18.364
"Hello, world! Eunice is here!"

03:19.449 --> 03:22.619
- I said that?
- I'm paraphrasing.

03:22.702 --> 03:24.245
- Well, I'm glad I could help,
I guess.

03:24.329 --> 03:28.207
- Good. I'd like to rent a room,
non-smoking, please.

03:32.170 --> 03:39.052
- ♪

03:39.135 --> 03:41.804
♪ Yeah Hey ♪

03:41.888 --> 03:45.975
♪

03:46.059 --> 03:47.977
♪ Huh Huh Huh Huh ♪

03:48.061 --> 03:49.979
♪ Huh Huh Huh Huh ♪

03:50.063 --> 03:52.065
♪ Huh Huh Huh Huh ♪

03:53.232 --> 03:55.193
{\an8}- Thank you so much
for this lovely dinner, Eunice.

03:55.276 --> 03:59.197
{\an8}And may I also say,
why are you here?

03:59.280 --> 04:03.076
{\an8}- Because I invited
Eunice to stay with us.

04:03.159 --> 04:06.245
{\an8}Apparently, I encouraged
her to stand up to Hoyt.

04:06.329 --> 04:09.165
{\an8}- And she'll be standing up to
Hoyt in our house for how long?

04:09.248 --> 04:10.750
{\an8}- Just for a few days...

04:10.833 --> 04:13.878
{\an8}or a week or until I can pin her
to an end date.

04:15.254 --> 04:16.880
{\an8}- Here's the gravy.

04:16.964 --> 04:18.216
{\an8}- She can sleep in Gabby's room,
right, Gabby?

04:18.298 --> 04:19.341
{\an8}- Yeah, sure.

04:19.425 --> 04:21.511
{\an8}Smiley, smiley, winky.

04:21.594 --> 04:23.012
- Gabby, no phone at the table.

04:23.096 --> 04:24.555
- I'm not at the table.

04:24.639 --> 04:26.391
- No phone at the island.
- Okay.

04:26.474 --> 04:27.684
{\an8}- Or in the mud room.

04:27.767 --> 04:31.688
{\an8}- Mm-hmm.
- Or in the living room.

04:31.771 --> 04:34.274
{\an8}Yeah, I probably
should've just taken the phone.

04:34.357 --> 04:36.150
{\an8}- This food looks delicious.

04:36.234 --> 04:39.320
{\an8}- Where did you order it from?
- I made it.

04:39.404 --> 04:43.408
{\an8}- This can be made
in our kitchen?

04:43.491 --> 04:45.326
- Funny.
Did you wash your hands?

04:45.410 --> 04:46.744
- Why? We're using a fork.

04:46.828 --> 04:48.746
{\an8}- Your father uses a scalpel

04:48.830 --> 04:51.624
{\an8}but he can't operate on somebody
if his hands are filthy dirty.

04:51.708 --> 04:53.751
{\an8}People die that way.

04:54.669 --> 04:56.379
- Mrs. Ebnetter is right,

04:56.462 --> 04:59.549
Hygiene is very important
for surgeons and eaters.

04:59.632 --> 05:01.467
Aaron, sweetie,
can you spell hygiene?

05:01.551 --> 05:03.136
- School ends at 3:30.

05:03.219 --> 05:05.221
I'm off the clock.

05:05.304 --> 05:07.932
- Aaron, you promised me

05:08.016 --> 05:09.392
you'd study
to retake your spelling test.

05:09.475 --> 05:11.060
- If you stop learning, honey,

05:11.144 --> 05:12.895
your brain
will shrivel up to nothing.

05:12.979 --> 05:14.981
People die that way.

05:16.566 --> 05:18.609
[knock at door]

05:20.153 --> 05:23.281
- Do you have
any anti-fungal cream?

05:23.364 --> 05:26.993
Someone ran off on me without
picking up my prescription.

05:27.076 --> 05:29.287
- Uh, no.

05:29.370 --> 05:32.874
But please don't touch anything
while you're here.

05:33.332 --> 05:35.084
- Fine.
I'll just suffer.

05:35.168 --> 05:37.545
- Maybe it's time for you
to suffer, Hoyt!

05:37.628 --> 05:40.673
Go ahead and scratch your
you-know-what off!

05:42.008 --> 05:45.428
Who's ready for turkey?

05:46.304 --> 05:49.432
♪

05:49.515 --> 05:51.934
- Uh, you
really don't have to do this.

05:52.018 --> 05:55.271
Rewashing the dishes, redoing
the laundry, remaking the beds.

05:55.354 --> 05:57.940
- Oh, were these made?

05:58.024 --> 06:00.985
- Well, I better go take out
the recycling.

06:01.069 --> 06:04.113
- Already done
and properly resorted.

06:05.406 --> 06:08.242
- No wrinkles.

06:08.326 --> 06:10.787
Man, I do love a tight bed.

06:10.870 --> 06:13.456
- I was sorry to hear
about your spelling test?

06:13.539 --> 06:15.291
I bet it made your stepmom sad.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.667
- She took it okay.

06:16.751 --> 06:18.044
- Made me sad.

06:23.216 --> 06:25.259
- Did you already wash up?
I didn't hear any water running?

06:25.343 --> 06:28.179
- Don't need it.
I'm dry clean only.

06:28.262 --> 06:30.473
- You don't want
to be filthy dirty, James.

06:30.556 --> 06:32.308
Let me show you my screensaver.

06:35.353 --> 06:37.396
- What is that?

06:37.480 --> 06:39.690
- That's a boy who didn't wash
behind his ears.

06:39.774 --> 06:42.276
His ears used to be here.

06:45.196 --> 06:47.323
♪

06:47.406 --> 06:50.576
- Well, here's something I'd
never thought I'd say.

06:50.660 --> 06:52.537
Sweet dreams, Mrs. Ebnetter.

06:52.620 --> 06:54.247
- Sleep tight.

06:54.330 --> 06:54.455
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

07:01.254 --> 07:02.922
- So you have a beau?

07:03.005 --> 07:05.550
- Do you mean a boyfriend?

07:05.633 --> 07:07.135
Yeah.
Noah.

07:07.218 --> 07:08.386
- Oh.

07:08.469 --> 07:09.804
That's so nice to have a boy...

07:09.887 --> 07:12.348
in the beginning,

07:12.431 --> 07:15.351
before you start
having to give things up.

07:15.434 --> 07:16.686
- What did you have to give up?

07:16.769 --> 07:18.146
- Oh, not much.

07:18.229 --> 07:20.314
Full ride to MIT,
modeling contract.

07:20.398 --> 07:20.898
They threatened Hoyt's
self-esteem.

07:20.982 --> 07:24.193
- Huh, you were a model?

07:24.277 --> 07:26.362
- Just high fashion.

07:27.446 --> 07:29.240
Are these shoes new?

07:29.323 --> 07:31.576
Hoyt thinks that buying new
clothes is frivolous.

07:31.659 --> 07:34.120
- So you can only wear
old clothes?

07:34.203 --> 07:35.121
- Relationships are
about compromise.

07:35.204 --> 07:38.207
You compromise and compromise,

07:38.291 --> 07:40.418
and pretty soon
you forget who you are.

07:40.501 --> 07:42.545
Then it doesn't hurt so much.

07:44.297 --> 07:46.382
Haha. I can tell you
stories all night.

07:47.216 --> 07:49.385
♪

07:49.468 --> 07:52.763
- Kids, could
you hurry up, please?

07:52.847 --> 07:55.266
- Might as well be yelling
at myself.

07:55.349 --> 07:56.559
- Children?

08:00.229 --> 08:03.149
- What is this?

08:03.232 --> 08:04.400
Have you guys had breakfast?

08:04.483 --> 08:09.071
- Mrs. Ebnetter made us eggs
and bacon and fresh biscuits.

08:09.155 --> 08:11.991
B-i-s-c-u-i-t-s.

08:12.074 --> 08:15.661
- Ah, look
at you spelling your food.

08:15.745 --> 08:16.996
And you look...

08:17.079 --> 08:18.456
clean.

08:18.539 --> 08:21.042
- Scrubbed up to my elbows,
teeth brushed and flossed.

08:21.125 --> 08:25.046
Mrs. Ebnetter says
a little blood is good.

08:25.129 --> 08:28.049
- Ew. But
at least you're flossing.

08:28.132 --> 08:29.675
So has Noah
flossed this morning?

08:29.759 --> 08:31.344
- I don't know and I don't care.

08:31.427 --> 08:32.720
- You didn't talk to him yet?

08:32.803 --> 08:34.388
But you're awake.

08:34.472 --> 08:37.390
- I'll see him when I see him,
if I see him.

08:37.475 --> 08:38.601
- Huh.

08:38.683 --> 08:41.145
It's like I have three new kids.

08:41.229 --> 08:43.438
Don't tell my old kids
but I like you better.

08:43.522 --> 08:45.524
Let's get in the car.

08:45.608 --> 08:46.776
- I'll drive them to school.

08:46.859 --> 08:48.653
It's the least I can do.

08:48.736 --> 08:52.031
I have to go buy some decent
cleaning supplies anyway.

08:52.114 --> 08:54.158
Come on, children.

08:54.742 --> 08:57.536
- Okay. Bye.

08:57.620 --> 08:59.956
- Eunice made me lunch
three days in a row.

09:00.039 --> 09:02.166
- Plus,
she straightened out the kids.

09:02.250 --> 09:04.335
She's the best thing that's ever
happened to this family

09:04.418 --> 09:05.920
and I'm including myself.

09:06.003 --> 09:06.963
- Heh.

09:07.046 --> 09:08.422
♪

09:09.548 --> 09:11.008
- Hi, hi, hi.

09:11.092 --> 09:12.677
[sniffs]

09:14.220 --> 09:16.222
I don't smell the kids.

09:16.305 --> 09:20.101
- Did they move?
- That's the smell of clean.

09:20.184 --> 09:23.479
- It's about time you went
lemony fresh on this family.

09:23.562 --> 09:25.648
- Mother, it's not me.

09:25.731 --> 09:28.067
Eunice Ebnetter is staying
with us for a few days

09:28.150 --> 09:29.568
and she's been pitching in,

09:29.652 --> 09:32.363
being helpful rather
than critical.

09:32.446 --> 09:34.282
- I play to my strengths.

09:34.365 --> 09:38.411
- Well, so does she,
and hers work.

09:38.494 --> 09:40.413
I just wish
I knew what they were.

09:40.496 --> 09:41.914
- I heard guests.

09:41.998 --> 09:44.458
I brought wine
and hors d'oeuvres.

09:46.085 --> 09:47.712
- Thank you.

09:47.795 --> 09:49.630
- Okey-dokey. I'll just check
on my kids.

09:49.714 --> 09:52.800
I mean, our kids-- the kids.

09:53.801 --> 09:55.845
[doorbell rings]

09:59.098 --> 10:01.434
- Just want to remind you that
Thursday night is garbage night.

10:01.517 --> 10:03.519
So throw your garbage out.

10:03.602 --> 10:05.688
I've already thrown
out my garbage,

10:05.771 --> 10:11.193
my annoying, nagging garbage
that I'm better off without!

10:12.778 --> 10:14.530
- Hey guys.

10:14.613 --> 10:16.532
- Hey, Gabby, I thought you were
going out with Noah.

10:16.615 --> 10:20.036
- I was. But I realized there's
more to life than some man.

10:20.119 --> 10:22.204
So I'm staying in to read this
book Eunice gave me--

10:22.288 --> 10:24.040
<i>There's More to Life</i>
<i>Than Some Man.</i>

10:26.500 --> 10:29.128
- Books instead of boys.

10:29.211 --> 10:30.338
How'd that Eunice do that?

10:30.421 --> 10:32.048
- That's what I was saying.

10:32.131 --> 10:34.633
It's like she flew in
on an umbrella.

10:34.717 --> 10:36.844
- Hey, Steph,
I'm washing my linens.

10:36.927 --> 10:37.845
Is there anything more powerful
than bleach?

10:37.928 --> 10:41.223
Something in the
radiaty-acid-burny category?

10:41.307 --> 10:44.352
But still safe on colors.

10:45.728 --> 10:47.855
♪

10:47.938 --> 10:49.690
- All right, we're
gonna peek in,

10:49.774 --> 10:53.486
steal Eunice's
parenting secrets and get out.

10:53.569 --> 10:56.405
- What you need to do
is steal her cleaning secrets.

10:56.489 --> 10:58.491
I can see myself in that floor!

10:58.574 --> 11:01.452
And there's a rug on it.

11:01.535 --> 11:02.745
- Elevator.

11:02.828 --> 11:05.164
E-l-e-v-a-t-o-r.

11:05.247 --> 11:07.416
- Very good, Aaron.

11:07.500 --> 11:09.251
I'm so proud of you.

11:09.335 --> 11:10.586
I told you you can be as smart
as you want to be.

11:10.669 --> 11:12.088
High five.

11:12.171 --> 11:14.924
- Ah, positive reinforcement.

11:15.007 --> 11:16.300
I could totally do that.

11:16.384 --> 11:17.635
I'm awesome at that, see?

11:17.718 --> 11:19.095
I just did it on myself.

11:19.178 --> 11:20.930
Way to go, Steph!
You're the best!

11:23.391 --> 11:25.893
- Okay, Aaron,
the next word is "loose."

11:25.976 --> 11:28.646
- Loose.

11:28.729 --> 11:31.065
L-o-s-e?

11:31.148 --> 11:34.902
- No, that's "lose" as in
if you keep spelling it wrong

11:34.985 --> 11:39.281
you'll lose your parents love
and end up alone and sad.

11:39.365 --> 11:40.658
People die that way.

11:43.702 --> 11:45.287
- James, I am so proud of you

11:45.371 --> 11:47.456
for washing your fruit
before you eat it.

11:47.540 --> 11:50.876
Even that banana,
which comes in its own wrapper.

11:50.960 --> 11:53.462
- I don't know
where this has been.

11:53.546 --> 11:55.047
- That's a valid point.

11:55.131 --> 11:56.465
And I validate you.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.299
High five!

11:57.383 --> 12:00.803
- I don't know
where this has been.

12:00.886 --> 12:02.805
- Way to be cautious.

12:02.888 --> 12:04.265
See, I'm nailing

12:04.348 --> 12:05.933
this positive reinforcement
thing.

12:06.016 --> 12:07.476
Thank you, Eunice.

12:07.560 --> 12:09.812
- Eunice isn't doing
anything positive.

12:09.895 --> 12:13.691
Eunice is doing
something diabolical.

12:13.774 --> 12:19.238
She is doing the dark arts
of mothering.

12:21.407 --> 12:26.328
- The what now?
- That dark arts...

12:26.412 --> 12:29.665
of mothering.

12:29.748 --> 12:32.793
Guilt, shame, fear,

12:32.877 --> 12:37.965
and the darkest art of all--
conditional love.

12:38.048 --> 12:38.883
- Ah, Mom, please.

12:38.966 --> 12:41.385
Nobody cares
about your made-up things.

12:41.469 --> 12:43.345
She's just better at this
than us.

12:43.429 --> 12:45.181
- Uh-uh!

12:45.264 --> 12:48.476
I didn't use any of that
and look how you turned out.

12:48.559 --> 12:50.352
- What?

12:50.436 --> 12:51.687
Was that a compliment?

12:51.770 --> 12:53.022
- Not to you.

12:55.566 --> 12:56.358
- Okay, I'll bite.

12:56.442 --> 12:58.944
What did you use instead?

12:59.028 --> 13:00.404
- Honesty.

13:00.488 --> 13:02.865
See,
I would straight-up tell you

13:02.948 --> 13:04.867
when you were being an idiot.

13:04.950 --> 13:07.995
Oh, by the way,
you're being an idiot.

13:08.496 --> 13:10.956
Hey, Steph.
What's up, Grandma Maggie?

13:11.040 --> 13:16.545
- Hey, Aaron, how about a snack
for my good speller?

13:16.629 --> 13:18.464
- Okay.
- But before I give it to you,

13:18.547 --> 13:20.299
I want
to hear you spell popsicle.

13:20.382 --> 13:23.552
Because I am positive
you can do it.

13:23.636 --> 13:27.598
- Popsicle.
P-o-p-s-y-c-l-e?

13:27.681 --> 13:29.350
- Uh, good try, buddy.

13:29.433 --> 13:31.018
You're only off one letter.

13:31.101 --> 13:32.561
- I'm so sorry.

13:32.645 --> 13:34.730
Stupid, stupid, stupid.

13:34.813 --> 13:36.232
Please give me another chance.

13:36.315 --> 13:38.901
I don't want to die alone.

13:38.984 --> 13:40.861
- So just
how dark are these arts?

13:43.447 --> 13:45.366
♪

13:45.449 --> 13:47.409
- Why is Eunice's bag
on the front porch?

13:47.493 --> 13:49.161
- 'Cause she's got to go,
Charlie.

13:49.245 --> 13:50.913
Look at what she's done
to these kids.

13:50.996 --> 13:52.581
- What? I don't see a problem.

13:52.665 --> 13:55.334
Great speller, super clean,
hates boys.

13:55.417 --> 13:57.586
And I smell lobster thermodore.

13:57.670 --> 14:00.089
Haha. Charlie like.

14:01.006 --> 14:03.175
- Typical man.
As long as there's a hot meal

14:03.259 --> 14:05.594
in front of him
our feelings don't matter.

14:05.678 --> 14:08.305
Stephanie, you don't need him,
girl.

14:08.389 --> 14:10.266
- See?

14:10.349 --> 14:11.433
- So Gabby's mad at me.

14:11.517 --> 14:12.601
What's new?

14:12.685 --> 14:15.771
- Watch this. James,
there's a $20 bill on the floor.

14:15.854 --> 14:17.147
- And it can stay there.

14:17.231 --> 14:20.276
Money's filthy. Why do you think
they're always laundering it?

14:20.943 --> 14:23.779
- Okay, that's disturbing.

14:23.862 --> 14:27.825
- And watch this, Aaron sweetie,
spell "disturbing."

14:27.908 --> 14:32.955
- D-i-i...

14:33.038 --> 14:35.624
I can't. It's too risky.

14:35.708 --> 14:37.626
Mrs. Ebnetter says
if I get it wrong,

14:37.710 --> 14:39.003
you won't love me anymore.

14:39.086 --> 14:40.170
- Huh?

14:40.254 --> 14:41.672
She's got to go.

14:41.755 --> 14:43.090
- So you'll talk to Hoyt?

14:43.173 --> 14:44.967
- Are you kidding?

14:45.050 --> 14:46.176
People die that way.

14:46.260 --> 14:48.304
♪

14:49.680 --> 14:51.765
[knock at door]

14:52.224 --> 14:54.476
- So she sent her goons.

14:54.560 --> 14:56.145
Come on in.

14:56.228 --> 14:59.273
You're being monitored
by security cameras.

15:00.733 --> 15:01.650
[door closes]

15:01.734 --> 15:04.486
- Smells like a foot convention.

15:04.570 --> 15:08.574
- Hoyt, you got a hole
in the back of your pants there.

15:08.657 --> 15:12.077
- You catch a breeze your way,
I'll catch a breeze my way.

15:12.161 --> 15:15.164
- But it's only been a few days.
Look how you're living.

15:15.247 --> 15:16.832
- Don't touch anything!

15:16.915 --> 15:20.336
When we get home
I need you to boil me.

15:20.419 --> 15:22.004
- This is my true self.

15:22.087 --> 15:24.882
Man in his natural state.

15:24.965 --> 15:27.051
Jealous?

15:27.134 --> 15:29.845
- Your true self
has got some mustard...

15:29.928 --> 15:31.347
everywhere.

15:31.430 --> 15:33.766
- Yellow stains for freedom,
my friend!

15:33.849 --> 15:35.726
- You know who's good
with stains?

15:35.809 --> 15:38.646
Your wife,
who could patch up those pants

15:38.729 --> 15:42.816
and your marriage over here
at your house.

15:42.900 --> 15:45.319
- Driving you nuts too, huh?

15:45.402 --> 15:47.488
Getting rid of that harpy is
the best thing I ever did.

15:47.571 --> 15:48.572
I eat what I want.

15:48.656 --> 15:50.282
I sleep where I want.

15:50.366 --> 15:53.577
And instead of endless chit chat
about sconces

15:53.661 --> 15:57.748
and emotional support...

15:58.707 --> 16:01.877
I can devote my time
to my real passion--

16:01.960 --> 16:03.003
painting my presidents.

16:07.257 --> 16:08.592
- Why is Abe Lincoln crying?

16:08.676 --> 16:11.512
- Because he's married.

16:11.595 --> 16:14.390
- They're all crying.
- They're all married.

16:14.473 --> 16:18.102
Except Buchanan and uh...

16:18.185 --> 16:19.311
me.

16:19.395 --> 16:20.646
[crying]

16:26.026 --> 16:27.861
- No, no, no.
You're still married

16:27.945 --> 16:31.156
and your loving
and scarily effective wife

16:31.240 --> 16:35.327
is right next door waiting
for you to ask her to come home.

16:35.411 --> 16:37.913
- Look at me!
She'd never want me.

16:37.996 --> 16:41.083
She's gone three days
and I turn into an animal?

16:43.544 --> 16:46.338
- Nah, nah.

16:46.422 --> 16:48.090
- There, there.

16:48.173 --> 16:49.967
Stop crying. It's creepy.

16:50.050 --> 16:54.138
- Oh, Charlie, she makes me want
to be a better man.

16:54.221 --> 16:55.347
She completes me.

16:55.431 --> 16:57.307
She's the wind beneath my wings.

16:57.391 --> 17:01.770
How I miss her so much.

17:01.854 --> 17:04.606
- Go next door
and say you're sorry.

17:04.690 --> 17:05.065
- I don't miss her that much.

17:09.069 --> 17:11.113
- Aah!

17:11.989 --> 17:13.615
♪

17:13.699 --> 17:15.951
- Kids, good.

17:16.034 --> 17:18.954
I want to talk to you.

17:19.038 --> 17:22.915
I think Eunice may have put
some ideas into your heads.

17:23.000 --> 17:24.960
- Better her than some man.

17:25.042 --> 17:28.130
- Gabby, I want to give you
another perspective

17:28.213 --> 17:30.966
about men and relationships
and all of that.

17:31.049 --> 17:32.509
- Relationships.
I know that one!

17:32.593 --> 17:34.970
- R-e-l--
- Aaron sweetie, as much

17:35.053 --> 17:37.890
as we want you to do good
in school and try your hardest,

17:37.973 --> 17:41.351
it's more important you know
we love you no matter what.

17:41.435 --> 17:43.145
- I love you too, Stephanie,

17:43.228 --> 17:45.814
even if you did say
do good in school.

17:45.898 --> 17:48.025
Superman does good.

17:48.108 --> 17:50.569
I do well.

17:53.238 --> 17:55.699
- Why was my bag on the porch?

17:55.783 --> 17:58.035
Is that your way
of putting a helpless woman out

17:58.118 --> 17:59.328
on the street?

17:59.411 --> 18:00.746
- See, kids?

18:00.829 --> 18:02.164
This is
what I was talking about.

18:02.247 --> 18:03.832
She manipulates you.

18:03.916 --> 18:06.168
What she just did-- guilt.

18:06.251 --> 18:10.672
It's one of the dark arts
of mothering.

18:10.756 --> 18:11.840
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

18:11.924 --> 18:16.345
- The others are shame,
fear, and conditional love.

18:16.428 --> 18:17.679
- All I was trying to do

18:17.763 --> 18:20.891
was to show some gratitude
for inviting me into your home.

18:20.974 --> 18:24.895
And, frankly, I feel very bad
about having this kind

18:24.978 --> 18:27.523
of conversation in front
of impressionable children.

18:27.606 --> 18:29.316
- Ah, see?

18:29.399 --> 18:33.195
Shame. She's trying to shame me
by saying I'm a bad mom.

18:33.278 --> 18:35.197
- Oh, I'm not saying you're
a bad mom.

18:35.280 --> 18:37.866
I'm just saying
that children exposed

18:37.950 --> 18:41.036
to this much conflict
in the home end up in therapy.

18:41.119 --> 18:43.872
- Ah, fear!
- And then prison.

18:43.956 --> 18:46.458
- Double fear.

18:46.542 --> 18:49.878
- Stephanie, what you're saying
is mean and hurtful

18:49.962 --> 18:51.547
and if you don't stop,

18:51.630 --> 18:53.465
I'm afraid we can't be
friends anymore.

18:53.549 --> 18:55.092
- Bam! Conditional love.

18:55.175 --> 18:56.885
Four for four.

18:56.969 --> 19:00.138
- Wow. I feel so played.

19:00.222 --> 19:02.975
- I have to remember this
for when I'm a mom.

19:03.058 --> 19:04.434
- Oh, no you don't.

19:04.518 --> 19:06.728
In this family,
we parent differently.

19:06.812 --> 19:08.063
- Oh, really?

19:08.146 --> 19:09.731
- What do you use?
- Honesty.

19:09.815 --> 19:12.609
As in,
I will honestly beat you down

19:12.693 --> 19:15.904
if you do not get out
of my house.

19:15.988 --> 19:17.239
People die that way.

19:19.324 --> 19:19.867
- What's that, Hoyt?

19:19.950 --> 19:23.662
Oh, I miss you too. Hehe!

19:25.330 --> 19:27.624
- And put that Hide-A-Key back
where it belongs!

19:27.708 --> 19:30.294
Next to that man going
through our recycling bins.

19:30.377 --> 19:31.503
[sighs]

19:31.587 --> 19:33.881
Yeah, I'm gonna
have to rehide that.

19:33.964 --> 19:36.049
♪

19:36.967 --> 19:40.262
- Come on, kids, we're late.

19:40.345 --> 19:41.889
Did you study your vocabulary?

19:41.972 --> 19:42.556
- I'll...

19:42.639 --> 19:45.225
do it in the car.

19:45.309 --> 19:47.352
- Yeah, Noah, that's fine.

19:47.436 --> 19:49.146
If you want to hang out,
I can skip rehearsal.

19:49.229 --> 19:50.689
- Can but won't.

19:50.772 --> 19:52.816
- Okay, fine.
I'll go to rehearsal.

19:52.900 --> 19:57.195
Hey, can you come
to my rehearsal?

19:57.279 --> 19:59.740
- At least the kids
are all back to normal.

20:03.577 --> 20:07.039
- See you later, Dad, if there's
nothing flesh-eating at school.

20:11.043 --> 20:11.919
- Did you forget to talk to him?

20:12.002 --> 20:13.003
- I didn't forget.

20:13.086 --> 20:14.379
I like him clean.

20:18.634 --> 20:20.761
- Eunice says I have
to live here now.

20:20.844 --> 20:23.680
At 4:00,
I'd like two eggs, coddled.

20:23.764 --> 20:26.850
Not too coddled,
with a side of dry toast.

20:31.730 --> 20:33.315
- ♪
